{
  "texts": [
    "Note that this cross-modal adaptation is also a key factor in our approach, as discussed in Section 6.",
    "Following a similar trajectory, MaPLe [26] introduces intermediate learnable to-kens within both the vision and text encoders, while making them interdependent at each level.",
    "They further demonstrate that adapting both modality branches allows for more flexibility in the downstream tasks.Adapter-based methods offer an alternative strategy and are increasingly studied in vision-language [14,55,61].",
    "CLIP-Adapter [14] learns visual adapters to combine adapted and original features.",
    "A few other methods propose to leverage the knowledge of these models while only accessing their final embedding state."
  ]
}